<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,249,1966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[324,424,1149,1174]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[324,424,1149,1174]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Belciana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of East Asian 
<taxonomicName box="[738,861,1149,1174]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pantheinae">Pantheinae</taxonomicName>
generic group including genera 
<taxonomicName box="[1229,1338,1149,1174]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1229,1338,1149,1174]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Belciades</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Anabelcia" authorityName="Anabelcia" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Donda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1353,1429,1149,1174]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Donda</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[151,265,1185,1210]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Anabelcia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[279,394,1185,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Viridistria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[279,394,1185,1210]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Viridistria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[450,595,1185,1210]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Diphteroides</emphasis>
, which could be characterised by green or greenish wing colouration with rather similar cryptic patterns. The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[650,750,1221,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[650,750,1221,1246]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Belciana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has predominantly a South-East Asiatic distribution, with thirteen species known from Central and South 
<collectingCountry box="[680,750,1257,1282]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[760,845,1257,1282]" name="Taiwan" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[856,958,1257,1282]" name="Thailand" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[969,1026,1258,1281]" name="Laos" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Laos</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1036,1147,1258,1282]" name="Myanmar" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1158,1253,1257,1282]" name="Vietnam" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1306,1408,1257,1282]" name="Malaysia" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
in the continental part, and in Sundaland, 
<collectingCountry box="[602,731,1293,1318]" name="Philippines" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[794,1015,1293,1318]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
where it is apparently more diverse, represented by isolated endemic species in the remote islands. Similar to many other 
<taxonomicName box="[1139,1265,1329,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pantheinae">Pantheinae</taxonomicName>
, the species of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,251,1365,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,251,1365,1390]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Belciana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are rather rare in the collections; therefore the records of the new species are expected in further entomological exploration of South 
<collectingCountry box="[555,662,1401,1426]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">East Asia</collectingCountry>
and especially its island part.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,249,1966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1437,1462]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Note.</emphasis>
In the course of the present study we examined all known species of the genus 
<emphasis box="[1212,1358,1437,1462]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Diphteroides</emphasis>
(typespecies 
<taxonomicName authority="Bethune-Baker, 1906" authorityName="Bethune-Baker" authorityYear="1906" box="[240,734,1473,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Diphteroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kenricki">
<emphasis box="[240,484,1473,1498]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Diphteroides kenricki</emphasis>
Bethune-Baker, 
<number box="[677,734,1473,1498]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" value="1906.0">1906</number>
</taxonomicName>
) described or referred as 
<taxonomicName box="[1025,1125,1473,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1025,1125,1473,1498]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Belciana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This genus includes seven species [
<taxonomicName authority="Bethune-Baker, 1906" authorityName="Bethune-Baker" authorityYear="1906" box="[251,634,1509,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Diphteroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kenricki">
<emphasis box="[251,271,1510,1533]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[288,378,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">kenricki</emphasis>
Bethune-Baker, 
<number box="[575,634,1509,1534]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" value="1906.0">1906</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hampson, 1926" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1926" box="[648,992,1509,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Diphteroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulea" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis box="[648,783,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">D. caerulea</emphasis>
(Hampson, 
<number box="[927,984,1509,1534]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" value="1926.0">1926</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1002,1108,1509,1534]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1002,1108,1509,1534]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">comb. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Prout, 1924" authorityName="Prout" authorityYear="1924" box="[1124,1436,1509,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Diphteroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="habroscia" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis box="[1124,1274,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">D. habroscia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Prout" box="[1291,1428,1510,1534]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" refString="Prout, A. E. (1924) Some apparently new Noctuidae from Sumatra, New Guinea, Mefor and Buru. Bulletin of Hill Museum 1 (3), 414 - 450." type="journal article" year="1924">
Prout, 
<number box="[1370,1428,1510,1534]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" value="1924.0">1924</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,257,1545,1570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,257,1545,1570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">comb. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Prout, 1924" authorityName="Prout" authorityYear="1924" box="[274,590,1545,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Diphteroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patricolor" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis box="[274,425,1545,1570]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">D. patricolor</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Prout" box="[444,581,1546,1570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" refString="Prout, A. E. (1924) Some apparently new Noctuidae from Sumatra, New Guinea, Mefor and Buru. Bulletin of Hill Museum 1 (3), 414 - 450." type="journal article" year="1924">
Prout, 
<number box="[524,581,1546,1570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" value="1924.0">1924</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[600,706,1545,1570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[600,706,1545,1570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">comb. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bethune-Baker, 1906" authorityName="Bethune-Baker" authorityYear="1906" box="[724,1100,1545,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Diphteroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis box="[724,842,1546,1569]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">D. serrata</emphasis>
Bethune-Baker, 
<number box="[1041,1100,1545,1570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" value="1906.0">1906</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Prout, 1924" authorityName="Prout" authorityYear="1924" box="[1114,1436,1545,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Diphteroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subserrata" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis box="[1114,1272,1545,1570]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">D. subserrata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Prout" box="[1291,1428,1546,1570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" refString="Prout, A. E. (1924) Some apparently new Noctuidae from Sumatra, New Guinea, Mefor and Buru. Bulletin of Hill Museum 1 (3), 414 - 450." type="journal article" year="1924">
Prout, 
<number box="[1371,1428,1546,1570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" value="1924.0">1924</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,253,1581,1606]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,253,1581,1606]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">comb. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
] distributed exclusively in New 
<collectingCountry box="[620,704,1581,1606]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Prout, 1924" authorityName="Prout" authorityYear="1924" box="[762,1066,1581,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Diphteroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sophronia" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis box="[762,910,1581,1606]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">D. sophronia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Prout" box="[924,1058,1582,1606]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" refString="Prout, A. E. (1924) Some apparently new Noctuidae from Sumatra, New Guinea, Mefor and Buru. Bulletin of Hill Museum 1 (3), 414 - 450." type="journal article" year="1924">
Prout, 
<number box="[1001,1058,1582,1606]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" value="1924.0">1924</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1073,1175,1581,1606]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1073,1175,1581,1606]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">comb. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1327,1436,1581,1606]" name="Indonesia" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(Sumatra). Despite the external similarity of some species to 
<taxonomicName box="[838,938,1617,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[838,938,1617,1642]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Belciana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, particularly the bluish-green ground colour of forewing and certain elements of the wing pattern resembling those of 
<taxonomicName box="[999,1099,1653,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[999,1099,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Belciana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the genus 
<emphasis box="[1232,1378,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Diphteroides</emphasis>
well differs from the latter genus by structure of male and female genitalia. The imago of the type-species, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Diphteroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kenricki">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Diphteroides kenricki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and its male and female genitalia are illustrated here (
<figureCitation box="[865,996,1725,1750]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="19.[151,263,1841,1864]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1821]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Belciana and Diphteroides spp., adults (25 – 30) and male genitalia (31). 25. B. pinratanai sp. n., female, paratype, Thailand, slide GB 8300 (GB); 26. B. pinratanai, sp. n., male, paratype, Thailand, slide MJP 707 (MJP); 27. B. scorpio, female, Thailand; 28. B. scorpio, male, North Vietnam, slide GB 7411 (GB); 29. B. scorpio, female, North Vietnam, slide GB 7365 (GB); 30. D. kendricki, male, Irian Jaya, slide GB 7354 (GB); 31. Ditto, male genitalia, slide GB 7354 (GB)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241477/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
Figs 
<number box="[922,996,1726,1750]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" value="30.31">30, 31</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1008,1040,1726,1750]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 45" captionStartId="23.[151,263,1841,1864]" captionTargetBox="[158,1426,223,1811]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1821]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 45. Belciana and Diphteroides spp., male (41) and female (42 – 45) genitalia. 41. B. scorpio, Thailand, slide GB / ZSM N 4215 (ZSM); 42. D. kendricki, Irian Jaya, slide GB 7372 (GB); 43. B. biformis, Sumatra, slide GB / ZSM N 4158 (ZSM); 44. B. hemodoides, Borneo, slide GB 7389 (GB); 45. B. sp., Irian Jaya, slide GB 7363 (GB). Most distinctive characters are marked by lines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241481/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
<number box="[1008,1040,1726,1750]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
). The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[1310,1436,1725,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Diphteroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kenricki">
<emphasis box="[1310,1436,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">D. kenricki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have simply straight uncus, strongly sclerotised tegumen with characteristic for the genus long lateral spines; strongly sclerotised narrow valva with strong costa, plate-like digitus, strong comb-like clasper with short wide and rounded harpe; the vesica of aedeagus bulbous, bearing a small patch of short cornuti at junction with aedeagus. The female has complex strongly sclerotised antrum, short sclerotised and ribbed ductus bursae and elongate corpus bursae. Herewith we confirm the separation of 
<emphasis box="[805,951,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Diphteroides</emphasis>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[1032,1132,1905,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1032,1132,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Belciana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has been done by 
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway" box="[151,346,1941,1966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2009) The Moths of Borneo, part 13, Family Noctuidae, subfamilies Pantheinae, Bagisarinae, Acontiinae Aediinae, Eustrotiinae, Bryophilinae, Aeroperoninae, Aventiinae, Eublemminae. Malayan Nature Journal, 62 (1 - 2), 1 - 240." type="journal article" year="2009">
Holloway (
<number box="[276,338,1942,1966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" value="2009.0">2009</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
